HEADWORD: Cheery
<hw>Cheer"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Displaying evident
cheerfulness; cheerful; lively; gay; bright; pleasant; <as>as, a
<ex>cheery</ex> person; a <ex>cheery</ex> hello</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> pleasant, sunny.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><q>His <qex>cheery</qex> little study, where the sunshine glimmered
so pleasantly.</q> <rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

